Additional Abilities

Additional abilities may be acquired after reaching crystal strength level 65.
Acquired abilities may be equipped from the Gear/Abilities screen.

Using an additional ability grants a special effect.
*Additional abilities have no impact on turn rate.
Although they do not add to the total number of turns, they do consume turns remaining during summoning or while receiving friend support.
Additionally, they cannot fill a summon gauge or EX ability recast gauge.
*An additional ability's capabilities varies with the character who acquired it.
*Special effects triggered by the same character do not stack, and the stronger effect will take priority.

Strengthening Additional Abilities

Perform a limit break three times on a bloom stone, and you can earn a passive that strengthens an additional ability.
To perform a limit break on a bloom stone, use bloom fragments on the Enhance screen.
An additional ability can also be strengthened by reaching crystal strength level 70.
